The paper deals with image representation and material categorization, which are both related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Completed Fisher Vector (CFV) framework involves encoding correlations and variances of local descriptors, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Principal Component Analysis (PCA) for decorrelation, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a more general framework for Fisher Vector, which could be considered a contribution to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
